        "created_at": "2022-08-25T15:23:46.341Z",
        "cooked": "<p>So for my 100 servers, I would need 100 land lines? I think that is obviously unreasonable.</p>\n<p>I also noticed that AsamK/signal-cli is a java application, which makes it a no-go right from the start, since none of my servers use java and I‚Äôm not willing to run something that enormous, to send a 10 byte message.</p>\n<p>Ideally, I would like Signal to work like <a href=\"https://letsencrypt.org/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Let‚Äôs Encrypt certificates</a>, you register your system with a simple <a href=\"https://github.com/acmesh-official/acme.sh\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">bash script</a> and it-just-works.</p>",
