        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-08-25T15:29:38.191Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"HighFrequencySignal\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"46724\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/highfrequencysignal/48/32390_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> HighFrequencySignal:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>So for my 100 servers, I would need 100 land lines?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>No, you can set up one client as the primary device and then link all the others to it. You wouldn‚Äôt be able to have them show up as separate contacts, but you could include the server information in the message so you know which one it was from. With a bit more effort you could create separate group chats for each server if you really wanted their messages to be separate.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"HighFrequencySignal\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"46724\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/highfrequencysignal/48/32390_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> HighFrequencySignal:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>none of my servers use java and I‚Äôm not willing to run something that enormous, to send a 10 byte message.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Those are pretty sad servers if they can‚Äôt handle Java. Even the Raspberry Pi can run Java extremely well.</p>",
