        "username": "HighFrequencySignal",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/highfrequencysignal/{size}/32390_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-08-25T15:33:54.226Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think it is obvious that I‚Äôm barking up the wrong tree. Java is a definitely NO for my use case (and servers), as I mentioned above. Finding phone numbers (or even a single one) for matching with a signal account is also unreasonable. I think I need another chat/messenger service entirely, something encrypted and lightweight.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your answers.</p>",
