        "created_at": "2022-08-25T15:37:05.118Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"HighFrequencySignal\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"46724\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/highfrequencysignal/48/32390_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> HighFrequencySignal:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think I need another chat/messenger service entirely</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Probably so. Signal is meant to be a messenger app for ‚Äúregular users‚Äù, not a lightweight highly-scalable solution for server status messages. That‚Äôs why the command line client is an unofficial community project and not an official client developed by the Signal team. What you are wanting to do is really outside of the intended use of the software, not that it isn‚Äôt entirely impossible, but you have to be willing to work within the constraints of what is available. If not, then you‚Äôll need something else.</p>",
